# Project structure

GitHub Pages playground: Vite apps under `apps/`, shared packages under `lib/`, built output under `docs/`.

```
apps/<app-name>/     # Vite app (kebab-case)
lib/<lib-name>/      # local npm package
catalog/             # portal / API metadata (YAML)
  workspace.yaml     # path + URL conventions
  entries/           # per app/lib metadata
docs/                # Pages root (commit builds)
  index.html         # portal (loads api/catalog.json)
  api/catalog.json   # static catalog API (generated)
  <app-name>/        # build output
knowledge/           # product intent, domain, incidents (not Pages)
blender/             # Blender assets (see blender rule)
tools/workspace-catalog/  # reusable YAML → JSON catalog builder
```

## Must

- New apps → `apps/<kebab-case>/`; finish with `npm run build` into `docs/<app-name>/`
- Add/rename/remove apps or libs → update `catalog/entries/` and regenerate `docs/api/catalog.json` (`cd tools/workspace-catalog && npm run build -- --root ../..`)
- Shared code → `lib/` (separation-of-concerns); UI tokens → `lib/theme` (ui-style skill)
- New apps → follow create-app skill
- Business intent / incident lessons → `knowledge/` (knowledge-capture skill); not into `docs/` builds

## Must not

- Hand-edit `docs/` builds (except `docs/index.html`, `docs/.nojekyll`, and generated `docs/api/catalog.json` via the catalog tool)
- Commit `node_modules/` or build intermediates
- Hand-maintain portal card lists in HTML — cards come from `catalog.json`